<div class="w-full max-w-lg mx-auto mb-3 bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-2xl shadow-sm">
    <details open class="group p-4 md:p-6">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer list-none">
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">
                How to get your Instagram data
            </h2>
            <span class="text-2xl text-gray-400 transition-transform duration-200 rotate-90 group-open:rotate-0">
                ▾
            </span>
        </summary>

        <ol class="mt-4 flex flex-col gap-2 text-sm text-gray-600 list-decimal list-inside">
            <li>Open Instagram and tap the <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900">☰ menu icon</span> in the top right</li>
            <li>Tap <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Accounts Center</span></li>
            <li>Tap <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Your information and permissions</span></li>
            <li>Tap <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Export your information</span></li>
            <li>Tap <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Create export</span></li>
            <li>Select <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Export to device</span></li>
            <li>Tap <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Customize information</span>, and check only <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Followers and Following</span></li>
            <li>Set the date range to <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900">All time</span></li>
            <li>Under Format, select <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900">JSON</span></li>
            <li>Tap <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Start export</span></li>
        </ol>
    </details>
</div>